		<description><![CDATA[Ron Burgundy is everywhere!]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Ron Burgundy is everywhere!</p>
<p>The promotion of Anchorman 2 was unconventional to say the least. Ron appeared as a band member on Conan O&#8217;Brien, and in numerous Dodge Durango commercials; he attended the MTV VMA awards and even showed up at the Olympic Curling Trials. Most recently he co-hosted a local North Dakota news program.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><iframe width="500" height="281" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/2b5IhzGuMPg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p>(Ron&#8217;s photo bombs are especially amusing.)</p>
<p>Ben &amp; Jerry even created an ice cream flavor in Ron&#8217;s honor, called “Scotchy, Scotch, Scotch.”</p>
<p><img class="alignnone" alt="" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-r5fBpwo0XmE/Uo_t0nm4cgI/AAAAAAAALv8/vIuUgAgEw0k/s1600/ben%2Bjerrys%2Bron%2Bburgundy%2Bscotchy%2Bscotch%2Bscotch%2Bice%2Bcream%2Bpint.jpg" width="227" height="254" /></p>
<p>Some think all the promotion is too much––they&#8217;ve had enough of Mr. Burgundy.</p>
<p>I think it is pure marketing genius, thinking outside the box of boring commercials, ads, and billboards. I actually watch and enjoy the Dodge commercials, as opposed to my normal habit of changing the channel. Not to mention how viral his videos have gone––all free advertising!</p>
<p>Keep making us laugh Ron!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
